<h2>Solar Incentives in Worcester</h2>
<p>Worcester residents can take advantage of multiple incentive programs that significantly reduce solar installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on the total system cost through 2032, then stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Massachusetts offers additional state incentives including the Solar Massachusetts Renewable Target (SMART) program, which provides performance-based incentives for solar energy production over 10-20 years. National Grid customers in Worcester can also benefit from ConnectedSolutions, a demand response program that pays solar-plus-storage customers for reducing grid demand during peak periods. Property tax exemptions ensure that solar installations won't increase your Worcester property tax assessment, while the system adds value to your home. These combined incentives can reduce the effective cost of solar by 40-50% or more.</p>

