<p>When selecting a solar installer in Worcester, prioritize companies with proper Massachusetts licensing, NABCEP-certified installers, and extensive local experience with National Grid interconnection processes. Look for installers who offer comprehensive warranties covering panels (20-25 years), inverters (10-25 years), and workmanship (10+ years). Top Worcester solar companies should provide detailed shade analysis, accurate production estimates based on local weather data, and transparent financing options. Verify their Better Business Bureau rating, read recent customer reviews, and confirm they handle all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork. Reputable installers will also explain National Grid's net metering policies and help you understand your electrical bill structure. Request multiple quotes and be wary of door-to-door sales tactics or high-pressure sales approaches that are unfortunately common in the solar industry.</p>

